{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 16,
  "title": "第十六章（歸根）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "至虛極也。守情表也。萬物旁作。吾以觀亓復也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "天物雲雲，各復歸於亓根。曰：靜。靜，是謂復命。復命，常也。知常，明也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不知常，㠵㠵作兇。知常容。容乃公。公乃王。王乃天。天乃道。道乃久。歿身不殆。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "得道之人，捐情去欲，五內清靜，至於虛極。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "守清靜，行篤厚。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "作，生也。萬物並生也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 18,
          "end": 19
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言吾以觀見萬物無不皆歸其本也。人當念重其本也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "芸芸者，華葉盛也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言萬物無不枯落，各復反其根而更生也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "靜謂根也。根安靜柔弱，謙卑處下，故不復死也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言安靜者是為復還性命，使不死也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "覆命使不死，乃道之所常行也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能知道之所常行，則為明。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不知道之所常行，妄作巧詐，則失神明，故凶也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能知道之所常行，去情忘欲，無所不包容也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 21
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不包容，則公正無私，眾邪莫當。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-14",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "公正無私，可以為天下王。治身正則形一，神明千萬，共湊其躬也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-15",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 30,
          "end": 31
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能王，德合神明，乃與天通。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-16",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 36
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "德與天通，則與道合同也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-17",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 40,
          "end": 41
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "與道合同，乃能長久。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-18",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 38,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能公能王，通天合道，四者純備，道德弘遠，無殃無咎，乃與天地俱沒，不危殆也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言致虛物之極，篤守靜物之真正也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以虛靜觀其反復。凡有起於虛，動起於靜，故萬物雖並動作，卒復歸於虛靜，是物之極篤也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "歸根則靜，故曰靜。靜則復命，故曰復命也。復命則得性命之常，故曰常也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "常之為物，不偏不彰，無皦昧之狀，溫涼之象，故曰知常曰明也。唯此復，乃能包通萬物，無所不容，失此以往，則邪入乎分，則物離其分，故曰不知常，則妄作凶也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不包通也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 21
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不包通，則乃至於蕩然公平也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 38,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "蕩然公平，則乃至於無所不周普也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 38,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所不周普，則乃至於同乎天也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 35,
          "end": 36
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "與天合德，體道大通，則乃至於極虛無也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 40,
          "end": 41
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "窮極虛無，得道之常，則乃至於不窮極也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 38,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無之為物，水火不能害，金石不能殘。用之於心則虎兕無所投其齒角，兵戈無所容其鋒刃，何危殆之有乎。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
